cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CL 

This paper analyzes the audience targeting patterns of newspapers using regression and gravity models. The use of regression models suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). The use of the gravity model suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing text data, which could place it under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves studying the influence of socioeconomic and political characteristics, which could place it under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
